com.facebook.buck.event.listener

Class AbstractConsoleEventBusListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.event.listener.AbstractConsoleEventBusListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BuckEventListener, java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleConsoleEventBusListener, SuperConsoleEventBusListener

    public abstract class AbstractConsoleEventBusListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements BuckEventListener, java.io.Closeable
    Base class for BuckEventListeners responsible for outputting information about the running build to stderr.

      • logEventPair

        protected long logEventPair(java.lang.String prefix,
                Optional<java.lang.String> suffix,
                long currentMillis,
                long offsetMs,
                @Nullable
                BuckEvent startEvent,
                @Nullable
                BuckEvent finishedEvent,
                Optional<java.lang.Double> progress,
                ImmutableList.Builder<java.lang.String> lines)
        Adds a line about a pair of start and finished events to lines.
        Parameters:
        prefix - Prefix to print for this event pair.
        suffix - Suffix to print for this event pair.
        currentMillis - The current time in milliseconds.
        offsetMs - Offset to remove from calculated time. Set this to a non-zero value if the event pair would contain another event. For example, build time includes parse time, but to make the events easier to reason about it makes sense to pull parse time out of build time.
        startEvent - The started event.
        finishedEvent - The finished event.
        lines - The builder to append lines to.
        Returns:
        The amount of time between start and finished if finished is present, otherwise UNFINISHED_EVENT_PAIR.
